The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 19: The new service tax rate, which was raised to 12 per cent in the Union budget, came into effect from April 18. Service tax was increased from 10 per cent to 12 per cent in the budget, which brought 15 more services under the tax net, taking the count to 96. Service tax collections have been projected to double to Rs 34,500 crore this year against the budget estimates of Rs 17,500 crore for 2005-06.

 Washington, April 19: The IMF today said India needs to speed up reforms, particularly in labour, infrastructure and power, to push growth.

 New Delhi, April 19: McDonald?s, which plans to expand to eastern India, is looking at the franchisee model for growth. It will invest about Rs 400 crore to set up more outlets across the country in the next three years. 

 New Delhi, April 19: The government has allowed 100 per cent FDI in coal to provide adequate quantity of the fuel to core sectors such as power and steel as well as to non-core sectors, coal minister Shibu Soren said today.

 New Delhi, April 19: Private power companies that build wholly-owned transmission systems would now have to sign agreements directly with state utilities, instead of an earlier proposal where the transaction was routed via a central government agency.




